43. Develop a regular expression pattern that validates a password based on the following criteria: at least 8 characters long, contains at least one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, one digit, and one special
character.
ANSER
<?php
$password = "Abcdef1!";

$pattern = '/^(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*\d)(?=.*[\W_]).{8,}$/';

if (preg_match($pattern, $password)) {
    echo "Password is valid.";
} else {
    echo "Password is invalid.";
}
?>

OUTPUT
Password is valid.
